## Alternative: Token/Imprint System

Instead of theft, what about **imprints**?

```javascript
// Original stays with creator
Original {
  owner: "@bilal",
  location: "bilal's vault",
  imprint_count: 0
}

// But can create limited imprints
function createImprint(original) {
  if (original.imprint_count >= 10) {
    error("This has been shared enough")
  }

  return Imprint {
    source: original.id,
    generation: original.imprint_count++,
    quality: 1.0 - (generation * 0.1),  // Degrades
    bearer: null  // Who currently has it
  }
}
```

The original creator keeps the source, but can only make 10 imprints. Each generation is slightly "fuzzier" - encouraging people to seek originals.

